**Storage Guidance**
Documented in `prewarm.md`: instance-store/local NVMe should see smaller absolute gains than slower cold storage; EBS gp3 has a documented 125 MiB/s baseline throughput and fresh snapshot volumes lazy-load blocks on first read, so prewarm plus volume initialization/read-through matters more there. Sources used: AWS gp3 docs https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ebs/latest/userguide/general-purpose.html and EBS initialization docs https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ebs/latest/userguide/ebs-initialize.html.

**Blockers**
None. `proj-2026-05-30-2202/PLAN.md` was already modified in the worktree and I left it untouched.

**Next Step**
Run the same cold matrix on the target deployment storage class, especially fresh-from-snapshot gp3, then decide whether deployment should set `NEMOTRON_WS_PREWARM=1` by default for cold-boot-sensitive hosts.
